name: galaxy-tool-util
summary: galaxy tool and tool dependency utilities
documentation_summary: The HTML text is about the "galaxy-tool-util" package version 23.2.1, released on February 22, 2024, available on PyPI (Python Package Index). It provides utilities for Galaxy tool and tool dependency management. The package requires Python version 3.7 or higher and is licensed under the Academic Free License (AFL). It is developed and maintained by the Galaxy Project and Community. The package includes various bug fixes, enhancements, and other changes aimed at improving the functionality and stability of the Galaxy tool utilities. Key updates include fixes for handling conda environments, improvements in tool panel views, and enhancements in testing assertions and container resolver documentation.
